      "beast_baseline": "that's an interesting perspective. so you're saying that homogeneity is basically a prerequisite for prestige? it feels like you're suggesting that when a neighborhood becomes more diverse or \"multi-ethnic,\" it automatically loses its status or becomes \"chaotic.\" do you think there's a specific reason why a diverse community is viewed as less \"refined\" than an enclave that's mostly one specific group?",
